author: wn.com
title: Trevor and Alexis Traina to host San Francisco fundraiser for Jeb Bush
text: Yes, there are Republicans in San Francisco, and Jeb Bush is coming to the Bay Area on Tuesday to collect checks from some of them at not one but two fundraisers. The lunchtime gig will be at the oft-swooned-over Pacific Heights home of tech entrepreneur Trevor Traina and his wife, Alexis, who is creative director at Swanson Vineyards. (Trevor’s mom is Dede Wilsey, the longtime president of the board of the Fine Arts Museums of San Francisco.) Yes, Traina gave to President Obama‘s 2008 campaign, but he’s been largely leaning right.
